The pieces of film (1 × 4 cm²) were placed in an oven (IKA Oven 125 basic dry, Germany) at 105 °C for 24 h to reach a constant weight. After that, the dried films were immersed in 50 mL of double-distilled water (DDW) at a temperature of 25 °C for 6 h and stirred at a speed of 100 rpm. Then, the pieces of film were separated from the water. After drying at 50 °C for 24 h, they were weighed. The solubility percentage of the films was calculated using Eq. (2)30.2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
